This paper deals with optimization and scheduling problems in a real-world application, which is a common topic in the field of Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Robotics (RO). The use of Map-Elites (ME) algorithm also suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization, which falls under the category of AI. The paper also discusses the ability of ME to provide diverse solutions, which is a topic of interest in the field of machine learning (LG). The problem of workforce scheduling and routing also involves the use of algorithms and data structures (DS) to efficiently manage and process large amounts of data. Finally, the paper discusses the potential application of the algorithm in practical domains, which suggests a focus on systems and control (SY).
